#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a Network Bridge"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create a network bridge, create a file in the <filename>/etc/sysconfig/"
"network-scripts/</filename> directory called <filename>ifcfg-"
"br<replaceable>N</replaceable></filename>, replacing <replaceable>N</"
"replaceable> with the number for the interface, such as <filename>0</"
"filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The contents of the file is similar to whatever type of interface is getting "
"bridged to, such as an Ethernet interface. The differences in this example "
"are as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <option>DEVICE</option> directive is given an interface name as its "
"argument in the format <option>br<replaceable>N</replaceable></option>, "
"where <replaceable>N</replaceable> is replaced with the number of the "
"interface."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <option>TYPE</option> directive is given an argument <option>Bridge</"
"option> or <option>Ethernet</option>. This directive determines the device "
"type and the argument is case sensitive."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The bridge interface configuration file is given an <systemitem class="
"\"protocol\">IP</systemitem> address whereas the physical interface "
"configuration file must only have a MAC address (see below)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An extra directive, <option>DELAY=0</option>, is added to prevent the bridge "
"from waiting while it monitors traffic, learns where hosts are located, and "
"builds a table of MAC addresses on which to base its filtering decisions. "
"The default delay of 30 seconds is not needed if no routing loops are "
"possible."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <option>NM_CONTROLLED=no</option> should be added to the Ethernet "
"interface to prevent <application>NetworkManager</application> from altering "
"the file. It can also be added to the bridge configuration file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following is a sample bridge interface configuration file using a static "
"<systemitem class=\"protocol\">IP</systemitem> address:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sample ifcfg-br0 Interface Configuration File"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"DEVICE=br0\n"
"TYPE=Bridge\n"
"IPADDR=192.168.1.1\n"
"PREFIX=24\n"
"ONBOOT=yes\n"
"BOOTPROTO=none\n"
"NM_CONTROLLED=no\n"
"DELAY=0"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To complete the bridge another interface is created, or an existing "
"interface is modified, and pointed to the bridge interface. The following is "
"a sample Ethernet interface configuration file pointing to a bridge "
"interface. Configure your physical interface in <filename>/etc/sysconfig/"
"network-scripts/ifcfg-eth<replaceable>X</replaceable></filename>, where "
"<replaceable>X</replaceable> is a unique number corresponding to a specific "
"interface, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sample ifcfg-ethX Interface Configuration File"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"DEVICE=ethX\n"
"TYPE=Ethernet\n"
"HWADDR=AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF\n"
"BOOTPROTO=none\n"
"ONBOOT=yes\n"
"NM_CONTROLLED=no\n"
"BRIDGE=br0"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For the <option>DEVICE</option> directive, almost any interface name could "
"be used as it does not determine the device type. <option>TYPE=Ethernet</"
"option> is not strictly required. If the <option>TYPE</option> directive is "
"not set, the device is treated as an Ethernet device (unless it's name "
"explicitly matches a different interface configuration file.)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifying the hardware or MAC address using the <command>HWADDR</command> "
"directive will influence the device naming procedure as explained in <xref "
"linkend=\"ch-Consistent_Network_Device_Naming\" />."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are configuring bridging on a remote host, and you are connected to "
"that host over the physical NIC you are configuring, please consider the "
"implications of losing connectivity before proceeding. You will lose "
"connectivity when restarting the service and may not be able to regain "
"connectivity if any errors have been made. Console, or out-of-band access is "
"advised."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Restart the networking service in order for the changes to take effect. As "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> issue the following command:"
""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "~]#&nbsp;<command>systemctl network restart</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An example of a network bridge formed from two or more bonded Ethernet "
"interfaces will now be given as this is another common application in a "
"virtualization environment. If you are not very familiar with the "
"configuration files for bonded interfaces then please refer to <xref linkend="
"\"sec-Create_a_Channel_Bonding_Interface\" />"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create or edit two or more Ethernet interface configuration files, which are "
"to be bonded, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"DEVICE=ethX\n"
"TYPE=Ethernet\n"
"SLAVE=yes\n"
"MASTER=bond0\n"
"BOOTPROTO=none\n"
"HWADDR=AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF\n"
"NM_CONTROLLED=no"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using <systemitem class=\"etheraddress\">eth<replaceable>X</replaceable></"
"systemitem> as the interface name is common practice but almost any name "
"could be used."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create or edit one interface configuration file, <filename>/etc/sysconfig/"
"network-scripts/ifcfg-bond0</filename>, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"DEVICE=bond0\n"
"ONBOOT=yes\n"
"BONDING_OPTS='mode=1 miimon=100'\n"
"BRIDGE=brbond0\n"
"NM_CONTROLLED=no"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create or edit one interface configuration file, <filename>/etc/sysconfig/"
"network-scripts/ifcfg-brbond0</filename>, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"DEVICE=brbond0\n"
"ONBOOT=yes\n"
"TYPE=Bridge\n"
"IPADDR=192.168.1.1\n"
"PREFIX=24\n"
"NM_CONTROLLED=no"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We now have two or more interface configuration files with the "
"<option>MASTER=bond0</option> directive. These point to the configuration "
"file named <filename>/etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/ifcfg-bond0</filename>, "
"which contains the <option>DEVICE=bond0</option> directive. This "
"<filename>ifcfg-bond0</filename> in turn points to the <filename>/etc/"
"sysconfig/network-scripts/ifcfg-brbond0</filename> configuration file, which "
"contains the <systemitem class=\"protocol\">IP</systemitem> address, and "
"acts as an interface to the virtual networks inside the host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Restart the networking service, in order for the changes to take effect. As "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> issue the following command:"
""
msgstr ""

